# Function to create the plot
create_plot <- function(data, filename) {
  p <- ggplot(data, aes(x = Response)) +
    geom_density(fill = "skyblue", alpha = 0.5) +  
    facet_wrap(~ Question, scales = "free", ncol = 6) +  
    labs(title = "Distribution of Responses for Math Anxiety Questions",
         x = "Response (1 = Strongly Disagree, 6 = Strongly Agree)",
         y = "Density") +
    theme_minimal(base_size = 10) +  
    theme(
      strip.text = element_text(size = 10),  
      axis.text = element_text(size = 8),   
      plot.title = element_text(size = 16, face = "bold"),  
      axis.title = element_text(size = 12),  
      plot.margin = margin(10, 10, 10, 10)  
    )
  
  # Save plots
  ggsave(filename, plot = p, width = 16, height = 10, dpi = 300)
}
